<paragraph id="64D414111C7A74DBDC9A31F1FD5F5DE5" pageNumber="123">
38. 
<taxonomicName id="C25183B3C636D9808AE673F165F363AF" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:134772" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formica cinerascens Fabricius" lsidName-HNS="Formica cinerascens Fabricius" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens">Formica cinerascens</taxonomicName>
, Fabr.?
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D87658D44D5A3005E1221BE41620443" type="description">
<paragraph id="3E39E714842FDCC65FD90013A68C5EEB" pageNumber="123">Worker, length 3 - 8 th of an inch; head large, eyes rather small posterior; jaws strongly toothed; thorax wide in front, narrowed behind with 2 glands on each side above; abdominal pedicle elevated, conic; abdomen oval; colour dull black, except the abdomen, which is glaucous green, and somewhat pubescent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DBB5A9736ED71A6D43326407BE328EC8" pageNumber="123">Female 1 / 2 inch long nearly; head smaller, thorax not so wide; abdomen long, oval; wings not reaching to the end of abdomen.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76C99E379F171DC6E12EB861CA1739FE" pageNumber="123">Male 3 - 12 th inch long; similar in form to the female, but with much narrower abdomen, and head still smaller proportionally. Warrior, 5 - 12 th of an inch long; head large; antennae short; eyes minute. '</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0932E56BE86AB4B10122C104853FCBC8" pageNumber="123">
This species lives in the ground in small societies. I have only seen it in the Carnatic. It is described as having the head fulvous, and a triangular spot on the abdomen, but as it is said by Fabricius to have been sent from Tranquebar, in the vicinity of which I have seen our present species, I think they are probably identical, and that the difference of colour is accidental, especially as there are only two species common in the Carnatic with glaucous abdomen, this and our 
<taxonomicName id="90A5556E18DE3CD5D45CF2E81AFD8E53" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:136046" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Formica" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Formica rufoglauca Jerdon" lsidName-HNS="Formica rufoglauca Jerdon" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoglauca">F. rufoglauca</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
